 :tx/rationale "Create task: ISP-FIX-8: Add hypothesis-ledger sanity tests for Phi against known-good stores. CONTEXT: The hypothesis ledger (hypothesis/* attrs, record_hypotheses(), calibration pipeline) was designed to catch formula errors via predicted-vs-actual comparison. No hypotheses existed for Phi. The discriminating test: Phi(entity with I+S+P attrs) should equal 0 — this would have FAILED with the broken implementation. APPROACH: (1) In bilateral tests or a new test module, create 3 stores with known Phi values: genesis (Phi=0), fully-linked entity (Phi=0), intent-only entity (Phi>0). (2) Record hypotheses using record_hypotheses() with predicted values. (3) Compute actual Phi and complete hypotheses. (4) Verify calibration error is 0 for the known-good cases. (5) Consider wiring into braid bilateral --commit so these sanity tests run on every bilateral cycle. ACCEPTANCE: (A) 3 hypothesis tests for Phi pass. (B) If Phi formula is broken, hypothesis (2) fails with non-zero calibration error. (C) Tests are regression-proof — they verify the formula, not the specific implementation. TRACES: ADR-FOUNDATION-014, INV-TRILATERAL-002. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/tests/ or crates/braid-kernel/src/bilateral.rs"
